The paper proposes a novel shape representation useful for analyzing and processing shape collections, as well as for learning and inference tasks. The paper discusses the use of deep learning and convolutional neural networks for shape classification and reconstruction, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the geometric structure of latent functional spaces, which suggests that it may belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses shape analysis tasks, such as highlighting the most distorted shape parts in a collection or separating variability modes between shape classes, which suggests that it may belong to the graphics (cs.GR) or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
